text: "Fatal Woman" may refer to: * the concept of the "femme fatale" * The Fatal Woman, a 1915 Dutch film * an alternate title for Femme Fatale, a 1991 film * Norine Fournier Lattimore, professionally known as "Dolores", also referred to as the "Fatal Woman of the London Studios" * "The Fatal Woman: Three Tales", a 1974 work by John Glassco * a 1952 novel by Patrick Quentin also published under the title "Black Widow"
title: Fatal Woman
